Chart.js organization chart plugin add drag and drop event



Javascript Source Code

The Javascript source code to do "Chart.js organization chart plugin add drag and drop event" is

(function($) {/*  w w w   .  d  e m    o 2 s  .   c  o   m*/
  $(function() {
   var ds = {
     'name': 'Lao Lao',
     'title': 'general manager',
     'children': [
       { 'name': 'Bo Miao', 'title': 'department manager' },
       { 'name': 'Su Miao', 'title': 'department manager',
         'children': [
           { 'name': 'Tie Hua', 'title': 'senior engineer' },
           { 'name': 'Hei Hei', 'title': 'senior engineer',
             'children': [
               { 'name': 'Pang Pang', 'title': 'engineer' },
               { 'name': 'Xiang Xiang', 'title': 'UE engineer' }
             ]
            }
          ]
        },
        { 'name': 'Hong Miao', 'title': 'department manager' },
        { 'name': 'Chun Miao', 'title': 'department manager' }
      ]
    };
    $('#chart-container').orgchart({
      'data' : ds,
      'nodeContent': 'title',
      'draggable': true
    });
  });
})(jQuery);


Open in separate window
View full source code

<head>
  <title>jquery organization chart -- drag &amp; drop</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
      <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://rawgit.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome/master/css/font-awesome.min.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://rawgit.com/dabeng/OrgChart/master/dist/css/jquery.orgchart.css">
      <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://rawgit.com/dabeng/OrgChart/master/examples/css/style.css">
      <script type="text/javascript" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.0.0/jquery.min.js"></script>
      <script type="text/javascript" src="https://rawgit.com/dabeng/OrgChart/master/dist/js/jquery.orgchart.js"></script>
  <style id="compiled-css" type="text/css">
      body {<!--  w   ww   . d   e m    o 2 s    .  c  om  -->
  font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 14px;

billboard.js Change the thickness of an axis



Javascript Source Code

The Javascript source code to do "billboard.js Change the thickness of an axis" is

var alarmFreqData = [
["x","al0","al85","al36","al9","al41"],["Freq.",5,2,1,1,1],
        ];//  w  w  w  .   d  e   m  o 2   s  . c   om  
        var tempForYAxis =  alarmFreqData[1].slice();
tempForYAxis.shift();
var yMax = Math.ceil((Math.max(...tempForYAxis))/5)*5; //https://dev.to/sagar/three-dots---in-javascript-26ci
var yTicks = [];
for (let i = 0; i < yMax; i+=yMax/5) {
  yTicks.push(i);
}
var chart3 = bb.generate({
              data: {
                x: "x",
                columns: alarmFreqData,
              //   [
              // ["x", "10", "21", "44", "77"],
              // ["alarm", 30, 200, 100, 400],
              //   ],
                type: "bar",
                colors: {
                  data1: "#ff00ff",
                },
              },
              axis: {
                x: {
                  type: "category"
                },
                y: {
                  //max: yMax,
                  tick: {
                    values: yTicks,
                    count : 5
                  }
                }
              },
              tooltip: {
                show: false
              },
              interaction: {
                enabled: false
              },
              legend:{
                show: false
              },
              bindto: "#AlarmFreqChart"
            });

                  tick: {
                    values: yTicks,
                    count : 5
                  }
                }
              },
              tooltip: {
                show: false
              },
              interaction: {
                enabled: false
              },
              legend:{
                show: false
              },
              bindto: "#AlarmFreqChart"
            });
  </script>
</body>
</html>

lodash.js Date _.now()



Introduction

Gets the timestamp of the number of milliseconds that have elapsed
since the Unix epoch (1 January 1970 00:00:00 UTC).


Since

The lodash.js library introduces the method
_.now() since version 2.4.0.


Returns

The method _.now()
 returns the following value:


    (number): Returns the timestamp.

    Example
    

<html>
<head>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/lodash/4.17/lodash.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
<script>

_.defer(function(stamp) {
   console.log(_.now() - stamp);
 }, _.now());
 // => Logs the number of milliseconds it took for the deferred invocation.

document.write("<br/>done");

</script>
</body>
</html>
